	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Am a newbie to EQ with an lvl 11 Bard in EC...grouping at Orc Camp 1.&nbsp;&nbsp; Bards are excellent..if you want to make friends and keep them.  Bards can provide an underlying regen for a group,  save food/water for medding and enhance tanking...all through a lil' bit of twisting.  When it comes to a last resort...Bards can aid tanks or enable a fast retreat.  No group is complete without a Bard..our abilities under-pin the success of a group with never a dull moment &lt;g&gt;.  If you like down time and sitting around choose another class...but if you like non-stop action at all phases of group play then be a Bard...born to rock 'n' roll.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
